<HTML>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<TITLE>MARSHALL WITTMANN  -- Heritage </TITLE>


<H3>MARSHALL WITTMANN </H3>
<B>DIRECTOR, CONGRESSIONAL RELATIONS/U.S. HOUSE</B>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/wittmann.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
Wittmann, who previously served as director of legislative affairs for the Christian Coalition, will work on a project that examines the relationship between taxpayers dollars and special-interest advocacy groups. 
<P>
A former deputy assistant secretary for the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services (1992-1993), Wittmann has extensive experience on Capitol Hill, having also served as a legislative representative with the National Association of Retired Federal Employees, and as a public affairs specialist with the National Treasury Employees Union. 
<P>
Wittmann holds both a bachelors and a masters degree from the University of Michigan.  He lives in Silver Spring, Md. 

