<html>

<title>Cyber Personality bio -- Heritage</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg"><center>
<h3><i>Heritage CyberPersonality </i></h3>

<img src=/heritage/miller.gif align=left hspace=7><p>
<code>[<a href="/heritage/cyberp/cyb-fam.html">Hot Issues</a>][<A HREF="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/thf-cyber/">Forum</A>][<a href="/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/_user/addForm/short">Register</A> -- Free!][<a href="cyberwel.html#about">About</a> Forums][<a href="/heritage/cyberp/cybarch.html">Column Archive</a>]</code> </CENTER>
 <P>



Karen Czarnecki Miller is the Director of Executive Branch Liaison at <a href="/heritage/">The Heritage Foundation</a>, one of the country's leading public policy research institutes.
<p>
A conservative research foundation, Heritage provides policy analysis in several broad areas of study: domestic and economic policy, and foreign policy and defense.  Some of the more specialized departments within the foundation concentrate on <a href="/heritage/dept_writeups/asian.htm">Asian Studies</a>, the <a href="/heritage/library/index/g7.html">United Nations</a>, and <a href="/heritage/library/index/h2.html">Congressional reform.</a>  
<p>
Miller is primarily responsible for maintaining contact with the Clinton Administration, educating the presidential campaigns on important policy issues, and overseeing The Heritage Foundation's <a href="/heritage/jobs/jobs.html">Job Bank.</a>  She also serves as a spokesman for the foundation on Heritage proposals and research findings in all areas of the Foundation's study.  She has been a featured commentator on numerous radio and television shows including "CNN & Co.", PBS' "This is America with Dennis Wholey," and <a href=" http://net.fcref.org/">NET NewsTalk Television.</a>  
<p>
Miller previously served as the foundation's director of <a href="/heritage/dept_writeups/95lect.htm">lectures and seminars</a> for three years, where she organized all public events for the foundation from welfare and education reform to ballistic missile defense.  If one of your favorite pastimes is watching C-Span, you may be familiar with Heritage's lectures and panel discussions.  
<p>
Prior to her work for the foundation, Miller worked in the Bush Administration as a special assistant for domestic policy and public liaison for Vice President Dan Quayle.  She was also a staff assistant in the Reagan Administration, where she assisted in the compilation of research data on the major domestic and foreign policy events which shaped the Administration.  This project served as the basis for President  Reagan's memoirs, and are on display at the <a href="/townhall/hall_of_fame/reagan/preslib.html">Reagan Presidential Library</a>.
<p>
A native of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, Miller is married to a Civil War buff from North Carolina who insists she has "southern traits."  Her husband, Matt, works on Capitol Hill, and they have two daughters. The first, Reagan Lee Miller, is named after President Ronald Reagan, the reason they both entered politics.
<p>
Miller has her B. A. and J.D. from The Catholic University of America in Washington, D.C.
<P><p>
<CENTER>
<p>
<center><code>[<a href="/heritage/cyberp/cyb-fam.html">Hot Issues</a>][<A HREF="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/thf-cyber/">Forum</A>][<a href="/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/_user/addForm/short">Register</A> -- Free!][<a href="cyberwel.html#about">About</a> Forums][<a href="/heritage/cyberp/cybarch.html">Column Archive</a>]</code> </center>
 <P>


